@node Overview
@prev Overview
@next Overview

@{FG Highlight}What is AmiSoxGUI.rexx@{FG Text}
----------------------

AmiSoxGUI.rexx is a graphical user interface for the sample converting program Sox.
You can convert one sample or even a whole directory of samples using AmiSoxGUI.rexx.

AmiSoxGUI.rexx is fontsensitiv, has an online-help (QuickHelp!) and it's very
easy to use.
@endnode

@node Requirements
@prev Requirements
@next Requirements

@{FG Highlight}Requirements@{FG Text}
------------

· >=OS2.04 (v37)

· AmiSox3.3
· triton.library (C) by Stefan Zeiger
· tritonrexx.library (C) by Jürgen Kohrmeyer
· rexxtricks.library (C) by Jürgen Kohrmeyer

You'll find all programs on Aminet.
@endnode

@node use

@{FG Highlight}Usage@{FG Text}
-----

This section only describes the usage of the GUI, please read the
documentation for AmiSox if you have any questions concerning that program.

AmiSoxGUI.rexx opens a window on the default public screen or a screen of
@{"your choice." link config}

Input@{u}f@{uu}ile:  @{" Name of sample you want to convert.                " link }@{" " link filerequester}
@{u}O@{uu}utputfile: @{" Name of the file that will be created by Sox.      " link }@{" " link filerequester}@{" " link Filetyp}

 @{u}A@{uu}verage:  @{" " link CheckBox}
 @{u}R@{uu}everse:  @{" " link CheckBox}
 @{u}E@{uu}cho:     @{" " link CheckBox} @{u}D@{uu}elay:   @{"           " link Slider}0ms  @{u}V@{uu}olume: @{"           " link Slider}0%
 V@{u}i@{uu}bro:    @{" " link CheckBox} @{u}S@{uu}peed:   @{"           " link Slider}0    Dep@{u}t@{uu}h:  @{"           " link Slider}0%
 @{u}B@{uu}and:     @{" " link CheckBox} @{u}C@{uu}enter:  @{"           " link Slider}0Hz  @{u}W@{uu}idth:  @{"           " link Slider}0Hz  @{u}N@{uu}: @{" " link CheckBox}
 @{u}H@{uu}ighpass: @{" " link CheckBox} Center@{u}X@{uu}: @{"                       " link Slider}0Hz
 @{u}L@{uu}owpass:  @{" " link CheckBox} Center@{u}Y@{uu}: @{"                       " link Slider}0Hz
 Vol@{u}u@{uu}me:   @{" " link CheckBox} Volu@{u}m@{uu}er: @{"                       " link Slider}0%

 @{"    Play in (1)   " link playin}     @{"    Convert (2)   " link convert}     @{"    Play out (3)   " link playout}


PullDownMenue:
 Project        Actions
 |__@{"About" link about}       |_@{"Convert Dir" link convertdir}
 --------
 |__@{"Help" link help}
 --------
 |__@{"Quit" link quit}

@endnode

@node about
@next about
@prev about

Opens a window with some copyright informations.
@endnode

@node help
@next help
@prev help

(De)-activate the Quickhelp. If selected move the mouse over an gadget and
you'll get a little help. Even if i included some help for you it's advised
to read the Sox-Guide.
@endnode

@node quit
@next quit
@prev quit

Opens an requester asking you if you really want to quit AmiSoxGUI.rexx.
If you prefer to quit AmiSoxGUI.rexx without requester, simply click the
closegagdet.
@endnode

@node convertdir
@next convertdir
@prev convertdir

Opens two dirselect requester. The first one for the source directory and
the second one for destination path. Now you have to select a filetyp you
like to convert the files in the source directory to.
If you don't select an filetyp AmiSoxGUI.rexx converts to standard-IFF.
@endnode

@node config
@next config
@prev use

@{FG Highlight}Configuration@{FG Text}
-------------

AmiSoxGUI.rexx knows one shell argument:

PUBSCREEN/K: name of publicscreen you would like to open AmiSoxGUI.rexx on.

Example: AmiSoxGUI.rexx DM.1



You have to adapt the pathes from @{FG Highlight}Sox@{FG Text} and your favorite @{FG Highlight}Sampleplayer@{FG Text}
in the beginning of the Arexx-Script.

/*
*** Configuration.
*/
/* path and name from AmiSox */
ASox   = "Sys:Audio/Sox"

/* path and name from your favorite Sampleplayer */
Player = "Sys:Audio/KSound"

/* Used path if you forget to choose one */
StandardPath = "ram:"

/* Used filetyp if you forget to choose one */
StandardSuffix = ".iff"

/* coordinates for output window */
WinLeftBorder	= 10
WinTopBorder	= 300
WinWidth	= 640
WinHeight	= 150
@endnode

